# AGENTS.md

> Per-swarm project conventions. This file is OPTIONAL. When present at
> `~/.hyvemind/swarms/<id>/AGENTS.md`, its contents are injected into the
> Worker prompt under the `### Project Conventions` subheader so the
> implementer has the right rules of the road before touching any code.
>
> Delete or expand any section. Empty sections may be removed entirely.

## Project Layout

- `<top-level-dir-1>/` --- <one-line purpose>
- `<top-level-dir-2>/` --- <one-line purpose>

## Coding Conventions

- Naming: <e.g. `snake_case` for Rust, `camelCase` for TypeScript>.
- Error handling: <e.g. `anyhow::Result` at boundaries, `thiserror` for domain errors>.

## Off-Limits Paths

- `<path/that/must/not/be/modified>` --- <why>
- `<vendored-or-generated-dir>/` --- <why>

## Testing Conventions

- Where tests live: <e.g. inline `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` next to code>.
- How tests are run: <e.g. `cargo test --lib` from `app/src-tauri`>.
